Rory Stewart (born 19 July 1996 in Perth) is a Scottish professional squash player. He reached a career high ranking of 40 in the world during December 2023. He has competed in multiple professional squash tournaments and has represented Scotland internationally.
In April 2025, Stewart won his 10th PSA title after securing victory in the Edinburgh Open during the 2024â€“25 PSA Squash Tour.
